</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F62FFFAFF26FC77FB75FF34" lastPageId="88" lastPageNumber="89" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F62FFF5FF26FC77FE46FB21" blockId="87.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Morphology. D VI–VII + I,9–10; A I,8–9; P 16–17. A small species with a moderately elongated body. Caudal peduncle deep, almost as deep as body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FF12FBBFFDE6FBB2" bold="true" box="[243,518,1081,1107]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">can be pointed in males</emphasis>
with the first spine longest (see 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FC8BFBBCFBB1FBB2" author="Francour, P. &amp; Bodilis, P. &amp; Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C." box="[874,1105,1081,1108]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref54712" refString="Francour, P., Bodilis, P., Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C. (2010) Inventaire des Gobiidae dans la Reiserve Naturelle de Scandola (Corse) et aI proximitei de ses limites. Contrat Parc Naturel Reigional de la Corse. Universitei de Nice-Sophia Antipolis, ECOMERS publ., Nice, 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Francour 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FC34FBBCFBE5FBB2" box="[981,1029,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
*). Caudal fin rounded, 2 large spinous scales on upper and lower fin base (barely visible, even in close-up photographs). Pelvic fins are separated, also hardly visible from lateral view. Scales present on body, usually poorly visible on photographs. Predorsal area naked (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FF08FB23FE7AFB21" author="Kovacic, M." box="[233,410,1189,1216]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1019 - 1023" refId="ref58016" refString="Kovacic, M. (2008 b) Live colouration, morphology and habitat of Vanneaugobius dollfusi (Gobiidae) in the northern Adriatic Sea. Journal of Fish Biology, 73, 1019 - 1023. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8649.2008.01918. x" type="journal article" year="2008">Kovačić 2008b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F62FFF5FF26FB4FFC17F9E5" blockId="87.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Live coloration. Head and body grayish with pale orange, reddish, rarely pinkish blotches and speckles, or indistinct bars of same colors on a paler background (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F62FFF5FD0CFB6BFCA0FAE6" box="[749,832,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1163,1187]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,181,1140]" captionTargetId="figure-18@23.[151,1437,181,1140]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 19. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Vanneaugobius dollfusi. Photo by S. Le Bris, Marseille, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601625/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), sometimes faded depending on the environment and the mood of the fish. Head mostly orange with irregular pale markings or speckles; 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FBADFA97FEE8FAAE" bold="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">the tubular anterior nostrils are white</emphasis>
. Usually 8–9 pale areas along back (from nape to caudal peduncle), sometimes becoming small white saddles. A series of typical 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FE20FADFFB9DFA92" bold="true" box="[449,1149,1369,1395]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">short pearly white bars arranged in 3-5 pairs on lower body</emphasis>
(depending on how much visible they are), usually interspersed with midlateral orange elongated blotches. First dorsal fin translucent with orange-red dots along spines. Sometimes an 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FD68FA27FAA1FA5A" bold="true" box="[649,1345,1441,1467]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">elongate dark spot on anterior basal part of first dorsal fin</emphasis>
, but not always visible in the field; this dark spot on the first dorsal fin is present in both sexes, but seems more commonly displayed by females (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FE73FA6FFD74F9E2" author="Van Tassell, J. L. &amp; Miller, P. J. &amp; Brito, A." box="[402,660,1513,1540]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="545 - 567" refId="ref65628" refString="Van Tassell, J. L., Miller, P. J. &amp; Brito, A. (1988) A revision of Vanneaugobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae), with description of a new species. Journal of Natural History, 22 (2), 545 - 567. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938800770371" type="journal article" year="1988">
<collectingRegion id="2B0BF83F3F62FFF5FE73FA6FFE20F9E2" box="[402,448,1513,1539]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Van</collectingRegion>
Tassell 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FDFBFA6CFDABF9E2" box="[538,587,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 1988
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FD41FA6FFCADF9E2" author="Kovacic, M." box="[672,845,1513,1539]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1019 - 1023" refId="ref58016" refString="Kovacic, M. (2008 b) Live colouration, morphology and habitat of Vanneaugobius dollfusi (Gobiidae) in the northern Adriatic Sea. Journal of Fish Biology, 73, 1019 - 1023. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8649.2008.01918. x" type="journal article" year="2008">Kovačić 2008b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FCB8FA6FFC0BF9E5" author="Louisy, P." box="[857,1003,1513,1540]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F62FFF5FF26F98BFC0EF9C9" blockId="87.[151,1437,973,2008]" box="[199,1006,1549,1576]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F62FFF5FE9EF98BFD76F9C6" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Pellegrin &amp; Fage" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[383,662,1549,1575]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Odondebuenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="balearica">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FE9EF98BFD76F9C6" box="[383,662,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Odondebuenia balearica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F62FFF5FD44F98BFC07F9C6" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kolombatovic" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[677,999,1549,1575]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Corcyrogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="liechtensteini">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FD44F98BFC07F9C6" box="[677,999,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Corcyrogobius liechtensteini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F62FFF5FF26F9B7FCD8F91E" blockId="87.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Habitat. Observed or collected underwater by SCUBA diving between 
<quantity id="2E379B383F62FFF5FC15F9B7FBBAF9AD" box="[1012,1114,1585,1612]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" unit="m" value="43.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="27.0">27–60 m</quantity>
depth, often found lying on sediment at the foot of rocky or coralligenous walls or slopes, quickly hiding in a nearby cavity or shelter (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FADCF9D3FF00F972" author="Kovacic, M." pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1019 - 1023" refId="ref58016" refString="Kovacic, M. (2008 b) Live colouration, morphology and habitat of Vanneaugobius dollfusi (Gobiidae) in the northern Adriatic Sea. Journal of Fish Biology, 73, 1019 - 1023. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8649.2008.01918. x" type="journal article" year="2008">Kovačić 2008b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FF0FF9FCFE3FF972" author="Francour, P. &amp; Bodilis, P. &amp; Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C." box="[238,479,1657,1684]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref54712" refString="Francour, P., Bodilis, P., Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C. (2010) Inventaire des Gobiidae dans la Reiserve Naturelle de Scandola (Corse) et aI proximitei de ses limites. Contrat Parc Naturel Reigional de la Corse. Universitei de Nice-Sophia Antipolis, ECOMERS publ., Nice, 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Francour 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FEBCF9FCFE71F972" box="[349,401,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
*; Le Bris 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FDB6F9FCFD6BF972" box="[599,651,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2015; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FD05F9FFFBEEF972" author="Glavicic, I. &amp; Kovacic, M." box="[740,1038,1657,1683]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref55156" refString="Glavicic, I. &amp; Kovacic, M. (2016) A quantitative sampling method for assessment of deep cryptobenthic ichthyofauna using trimix diving. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 46 (1), 43 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2016.46.1.06" type="journal article" year="2016">Glavičić &amp; Kovačić 2016</bibRefCitation>
; Glavičić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FB65F9FCFB57F972" box="[1156,1207,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2016; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FAF0F9FFFF34F956" author="Dubas, R. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P." pageId="87" pageNumber="88" refId="ref53088" refString="Dubas, R., Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P. (2018) Signalisation de / Record of Vanneaugobius dollfusi, 26 December 2018 (obs. 09 June 2018, photo  4676). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2018">
Dubas 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FA83F9FCFA75F972" box="[1378,1429,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Most of the collected specimens were caught deeper, mostly with beam trawls between 
<quantity id="2E379B383F62FFF5FB3AF91BFAAEF959" box="[1243,1358,1693,1720]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0699999999999998" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.54" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" unit="m" value="107.0" valueMax="160.0" valueMin="54.0">54–160 m</quantity>
depth, on different habitats: coralligenous or rocky grounds, maërl, deep algal beds, shell debris, sand, mud (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FAFEF947FED7F91E" author="Pallaoro, A. &amp; Kovacic, M." pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="255 - 257" refId="ref62496" refString="Pallaoro, A. &amp; Kovacic, M. (2000) Vanneaugobius dollfusi Brownell, 1978 a rare fish new to the Adriatic Sea. Journal of Fish Biology, 55, 255 - 257. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8649.2000. tb 00791. x" type="journal article" year="2000">Pallaoro &amp; Kovačić 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FEA0F963FDDAF91E" author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J." box="[321,570,1765,1791]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="5 - 19" refId="ref50326" refString="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J. (2004) Gobioid fishes from the north eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: new records and rarely found species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 105 B, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="2004">Ahnelt &amp; Dorda 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FDA5F963FCCDF91E" author="Ordines, F. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Vivas, M. &amp; Garcia-Ruiz, C. &amp; Guijarro, B." box="[580,813,1765,1792]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="275 - 282" refId="ref62095" refString="Ordines, F., Kovacic, M., Vivas, M., Garcia-Ruiz, C. &amp; Guijarro, B. (2019 a) Westernmost Mediterranean records of three gobiid species (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49, 275 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02604" type="journal article" year="2019">
Ordines 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FD45F960FD35F91E" box="[676,725,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2019a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F62FFF5FF26F88FFE71F839" blockId="87.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Geographic distribution. Eastern Atlantic and northern Mediterranean species. 
<typeStatus id="3674887F3F62FFF5FB86F88CFB49F8C5" box="[1127,1193,1802,1828]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Types</typeStatus>
collected in 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F62FFF5FAA8F88FFA79F8C2" box="[1353,1433,1801,1827]" name="Morocco" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Agadir</collectingCountry>
, Atlantic coast of 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F62FFF5FEB9F8A8FE5DF8A9" box="[344,445,1838,1864]" name="Morocco" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FE2DF8ABFD99F8A6" author="Brownell, C. L." box="[460,633,1837,1863]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="135 - 145" refId="ref52520" refString="Brownell, C. L. (1978) Vanneaugobius dollfusi, a new genus and species of small gobiid with divided ventrals from Morocco (Pisces, Gobioidei). Transactions of the Royal Society of South Africa, 43 (2), 135 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00359197809520233" type="journal article" year="1978">Brownell 1978</bibRefCitation>
). Known in the Mediterranean from the Balearic Islands (Ordines 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FA85F8A8FA75F8A6" box="[1380,1429,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2019) to the Aegean Sea, Peloponnese (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FDB3F8D7FCADF88A" author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J." box="[594,845,1873,1899]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="5 - 19" refId="ref50326" refString="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J. (2004) Gobioid fishes from the north eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: new records and rarely found species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 105 B, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="2004">Ahnelt &amp; Dorda 2004</bibRefCitation>
); records include 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F62FFF5FBF2F8D4FB82F88D" box="[1043,1122,1874,1900]" name="France" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">France</collectingCountry>
, Gulf of Lion (Le Bris 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FA85F8D4FA75F88A" box="[1380,1429,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2015), French Riviera (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FE40F8F3FD60F86E" author="Duhau, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[417,640,1909,1936]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" refId="ref53499" refString="Duhau, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2020 c) Signalisation de / Record of Vanneaugobius dollfusi, 24 December 2020 (obs. 20 August 2020, photo  5819). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2020">
Duhau 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FE14F8F0FDC8F86E" box="[501,552,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2020c
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F62FFF5FD74F8F3FD0BF86E" box="[661,747,1909,1935]" name="France" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Corsica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FD1BF8F3FC09F86E" author="Francour, P. &amp; Bodilis, P. &amp; Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C." box="[762,1001,1909,1936]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref54712" refString="Francour, P., Bodilis, P., Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C. (2010) Inventaire des Gobiidae dans la Reiserve Naturelle de Scandola (Corse) et aI proximitei de ses limites. Contrat Parc Naturel Reigional de la Corse. Universitei de Nice-Sophia Antipolis, ECOMERS publ., Nice, 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Francour 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FC88F8F0FC7CF86E" box="[873,924,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
*), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F62FFF5FBEBF8F3FBDEF86E" box="[1034,1086,1909,1935]" name="Italy" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Italy</collectingCountry>
, Strait of 
<collectingRegion id="2B0BF83F3F62FFF5FB51F8F3FB11F86E" box="[1200,1265,1909,1935]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Sicily</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FAE0F8F3FF33F852" author="Consoli, P. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Battaglia, P. &amp; Romeo, T. &amp; Scotti, G. &amp; Andaloro, F. &amp; Patzner, R. A." pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="263 - 268" refId="ref52726" refString="Consoli, P., Kovacic, M., Battaglia, P., Romeo, T., Scotti, G., Andaloro, F. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (2019) First record of two gobiid fish from the Strait of Sicily (central Mediterranean Sea): Odondebuenia balearica (Pellegrin &amp; Fage, 1907) and Vanneaugobius dollfusi (Brownell, 1978). Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 60, 263 - 268. https: // doi. org / 10.21411 / CBM. A. 36 F 385 CB" type="journal article" year="2019">
Consoli 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FA82F8F0FA75F86E" box="[1379,1429,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F62FFF5FF06F81FFEC8F852" box="[231,296,1945,1971]" name="Malta" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Malta</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FED9F81FFD8AF852" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J." box="[312,618,1945,1971]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="287 - 296" refId="ref58780" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J. (2019) Twelve new records of gobies and clingfishes (Pisces: Teleostei) significantly increase small benthic fish diversity of Maltese waters. Mediterranean Marine Science, 20, 287 - 296. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 19816" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Schembri 2019</bibRefCitation>
) and the Adriatic Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FC8CF81FFB73F852" author="Pallaoro, A. &amp; Kovacic, M." box="[877,1171,1945,1971]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="255 - 257" refId="ref62496" refString="Pallaoro, A. &amp; Kovacic, M. (2000) Vanneaugobius dollfusi Brownell, 1978 a rare fish new to the Adriatic Sea. Journal of Fish Biology, 55, 255 - 257. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8649.2000. tb 00791. x" type="journal article" year="2000">Pallaoro &amp; Kovačić 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FB7CF81FFA78F852" author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J." box="[1181,1432,1945,1971]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="5 - 19" refId="ref50326" refString="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Dorda, J. (2004) Gobioid fishes from the north eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: new records and rarely found species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 105 B, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="2004">Ahnelt &amp; Dorda 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F62FFF5FF76F83BFE65F839" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. &amp; Kirincic, M. &amp; Zanella D." box="[151,389,1981,2008]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="435 - 445" refId="ref58952" refString="Kovacic, M., Sanda, R., Kirincic, M. &amp; Zanella D. (2012 b) Geographic distribution of gobies (Gobiidae) in the Adriatic Sea with thirteen new records for its southern part. Cybium, 36, 435 - 445. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2012 - 363 - 003" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F62FFF5FF1AF838FECDF836" box="[251,301,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2012b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F6DFFFAFF26FF11FB75FF34" blockId="88.[151,1436,151,214]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
* Although misidentified in the cited report, three good photographs allow for a positive identification of 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F6DFFFAFA65FF11FF0BFF34" authorityName="Brownell" authorityYear="1978" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Vanneaugobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dollfusi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F6DFFFAFA65FF11FA75FF51" box="[1412,1429,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F6DFFFAFF76FF3DFF0BFF34" box="[151,235,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">dollfusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which makes them the first French record of this species). See also 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F6DFFFAFC0EFF3DFB71FF34" author="Louisy, P." box="[1007,1169,186,213]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy (2015)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
